metadata.name: Stroll
metadata.description:
Stroll:
December 11, 2021

Regardless of the temperature, Chicagoans find a way to get outside and enjoy the Lake Shore trail. 

This spot is a wonderful and normally busy intersection typically filled with walkers, runners, and bikers trying to get to their next destination. 

In the winter however, it's reserved only for the brave and bold who can handle our chilly (and sometimes extremely) cold temps.
